product_name: YSL Libre Flowers & Flames Eau De Parfum 50ml
description: Libre Flowers & Flames Is A New Sultry Floral Blast. A Sexy Warm Reinterpratation Of Libre, Deliberatly Sensual & Floral. The Hot & Powerful Lily From The Desert Blends With The Solar & Creamy Coco Palm Tree Flower, For A Blazing Yet Comforting Scent. Fragrance Notes: Top Notes: Lavender Heart & Bergamotte Essence Heart Notes: Lily Flower accord, Palm Tree flower accord, Orange blossom, Diva Lavender Base Notes: Vanilla

product_name: YSL Myslf Eau De Parfum 60ml
description: My scent, MYSLF - the expression of the man you are, with all your nuances. A statement of modern masculinity, embracing all his facets and emotions. The first YSL BEAUTY woody floral scent for a contrasted trail of modernity.  How to use:  Perfume on the 3 pulse points: wrist, inner elbow and neck.

description: My scent, MYSLF - the expression of the man you are, with all your nuances. A statement of modern masculinity, embracing all his facets and emotions. product_name: VOK Crème De Menthe Liqueur 500ml
description: Crème de Menthe Liqueur is a clean and crisp tasting liqueur made by blending an assortment of mint essences. Its a versatile liqueur that can be enjoyed as an after dinner drink, a simple mixer or the key to a number of delicious cocktails. Alcohol:  17%

product_name: YSL Y Reno Eau De Toilette 100ml
description: Creative. Doer. Accomplished.  How to use:  Perfume on the 3 pulse points: wrist, inner elbow and neck. Notes: - Bergamot Essence Aldeyhdes Ginger Essence - Lavander Heart Geranium Heart Clary sage Heart - Cedarwood Essence Olibanium Essence Ambergris accord

product_name: YSL Mon Paris Fragrance Discovery Miniature Set
description: Discover this exclusive 4-piece miniature set, featuring Mon Paris Eau de Parfum, a sweet floral perfume for women; Mon Paris Eau de Toilette Lumière, a light and dazzling fruity floral perfume capturing the essence of spring in the city of love; and Mon Paris Intensément, the new daring take on the classic Eau de Parfum. This set contains:  2 x 7.5ml YSL Mon Paris Eau De Parfum, 1 x 7.5ml Mon Paris Eau De Toilette Lumière, 1 x 7.5ml Mon Paris Intensément How to use:  Apply fragrance on the warmer areas of the body: behind your neck, onto the inside of your wrist and underneath your earlobes. Alternatively, spray generously in front of you and walk forward to immerse yourself in the scent. Apply Rouge Pur Couture starting at the center of the lip and gliding to the corners. Then reverse the movement for maximum color impact. Start applying at the root of the lash on the outside of the eye. Apply the brush to the lash, pushing upwards and outwards at the same time with a zig-zag type of movement. On the inner & bottom lashes, use just the tip of the brush and apply to individual lashes.

product_name: Viktor & Rolf Ruby Orchid Eau De Parfum 50ml
description: Flowerbomb Ruby Orchid by Viktor&Rolf is a Floral Fruity Gourmand fragrance for women. Flowerbomb Ruby Orchid was launched in 2021.  Top notes are Peach and Vine; middle note is Orchid; base note is Vanilla Bean.

product_name: VOK Peach Liqueur 500ml
description: Peach Liqueur is the most recent addition to the portfolio and delivers the juicy flavour of fresh, ripe peaches. Vok Peach Liqueur brings a fruity depth in some of the most delicious cocktails recipes. Alcohol:  17%

product_name: YSL Mon Paris Lumiere Eau de Toilette 50ml
description:
What it is 
 Intoxicating floral notes of datura flower, white lotus, and rose absolute are contrasted by fruity top notes of pear, lemon and black currant to create this sparkling feminine fragrance. A light and dazzling fruity floral perfume, Mon Paris Eau de Toilette Lumière captures the essence of spring in the city of love. About the fragrance The lavalliere on the neck of the Mon Paris Lumière bottle takes on a new sophistication. Inspired by Saint Laurent's transparent blouses, a sheath of black organza let's the nude-colored satin sparkle through.

product_name: YSL Libre Eau de Toilette 90ml
description: LIBRE, the new Eau de Toilette by Yves Saint Laurent. The fragrance of a sensual & irreverent woman unveiling a new undressed freedom, the freedom to live everything on the skin. LIBRE, THE NEW EAU DE TOILETTE BY YVES SAINT LAURENT Created by the master perfumers Anne Flipo & Carlos Benaim to unveil a new sensual & undressed freedom, The freedom to live everything on the skin. With initiatives of exceptional sourcing around the world, YSL BEAUTY selects precious natural ingredients that define the uniqueness of the scent of freedom. WHAT IT IS The iconic structure of LIBRE, a tension between noble orange blossom from Morocco and sustainably sourced lavender from France, exclusively crafted for Yves Saint Laurent, is reinterpreted in a modern, bright and fresh sensuality. The carnal femininity of orange blossom absolute is infused with a pure white tea accord, exacerbating the warm-cold duality of the fragrance to leave a shivering yet sun-kissed sensuous pleasure. The iconic LIBRE IT-bottle is reinvented in a new elongated shape whose vertical extension clashes with the couture extravagance of the gold oversize horizontal Cassandre bent & nailed into the glass. Libre Eau de Toilette encapsulates a new delicate golden pink fragrance shade, celebrating femininity on the edge of nude. The embodiment of a new undressed freedom.

description: The world's leading brand of premium tequila, a dark amber with copper highlights that spends 3 years in French oak. Rich in flavour, smooth, rounded with spicy agave taste. It has aromas of oak driven agave with caramel, vanilla and toasted coconut, and a pleasantly spicy finish.

product_name: 1800 Tequila Cristalino 700ml
description: An ultra-premium clear Añejo Tequila finished in port wine casks. 1800® Cristalino is a beautiful contradiction. It is aged in French and American oak barrels, married together, then rested in port wine casks. Finally, it is meticulously filtered to crystal clear clarity while retaining the depth and complexity of Añejo along with the silky smoothness of a Claro. Alcohol:  35%

product_name: Absolut Vanilla 1L
description: Absolut Vanilia is rich, robust and complex. The sweet accentuating qualities and creamy flavour of vanilla makes it just as delicious, neat as in cocktails. Taste:  Rich, robust and complex. It has a distinct character of vanilla, notes of butterscotch and hints of dark chocolate. The finish is long, rich and smooth. Alcohol:  38%

description: Blue Curacao Liqueur adds its distinctive vibrant blue colour to many classic cocktail recipes. This orange flavoured liqueur resembles the dried peel of oranges found on the Caribbean Island of Curacao. Alcohol:  17%

description: An easy pouch full of delicious Twix bars in a mini format. Share them with all your friends or family - there's plenty to go round. The cool minimalism of the face leaves room for some fun experimentation with the bracelet. T109.610.16.037.00

description: Arnott's Tim Tam Classic Dark biscuits are made with a mouth-watering combination of crunchy biscuit, luscious cream centre, wrapped in a smooth white chocolate coating.

Color: Clear Taste: Rich and intense with the fresh and fruity character of ripened raspberries. The finish is long and berry 38% Alcohol

product_name: The Singleton Radiant Spring Garden Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L
description: Inspired by springtime gardens with blossoming fruit trees. This whisky has been matured in our Select White Oak casks. The result is an exceptional expression of Glendullan’s quintessential bright and fruity character.  Alcohol:  40%

product_name: The Botanist Islay Dry Gin 200ml 46%
description: The Botanist is a gin of layered complexity. A progressive exploration of the botanical heritage of the isle of Islay. Nine classic gin botanicals are augmented by 22 local herbs and flowers, foraged responsibly and by hand from the hills, shores and bogs of this fertile Hebridean island. This fascinating seasonal cocktail is then slow "simmer" distilled in a unique Lomond pot-still. Affectionately known as "Ugly Betty" by the master distiller Jim McEwan, the still prefers to work at low-pressure and won't be rushed. So the precious botanicals are gently coaxed into releasing their complex, signature aromatics. The result is quicksilver: a highly distinctive, complex, floral gin with impeccable provenance; a truly artisanal, hand-crafted labour of love.

product_name: The Botanist Gin 1L
description: For this, “The Botanist”, small-batch, artisanal Islay gin we use nine of the classic gin aromatics – orris root, cassia bark, coriander seed, etc – and augment these with a heady harvest of 22 local botanicals, hand-picked by our expert foraging team from the windswept hills, peat bogs and Atlantic shores of this Hebridean island of Islay. Alcohol:  46%

product_name: The Glenlivet 12 Yo Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L 40%
description:
The Glenlivet 12 Year Old Single Malt Scotch Whisky represents the signature style of The Glenlivet distillery. This iconic Single Malt is matured in European and American oak casks. The double oak maturation process imparts vanilla notes and gives The Glenlivet 12 Year Old its distinctive smoothness. Fruity and exceptionally well-balanced The Glenlivet 12 Year Old has a delicate yet complex character.
 Nose: Fruity, summer-like fragrances Taste: Well-balanced and fruity with intense pineapple notes

product_name: The Jelly Bean Factory Pop-A-Bean
description: Ready for flavour? At The Jelly Bean Factory we're obsessed with flavour. You too? Good. Join us in our flavour adventure. The Pop-a-bean one bean pops out per time! We've got 36 HUGE flavours waiting for you. We bet you can't just eat one. The Jelly Bean Factory. YES. That's flavour.

product_name: Wynns Michael Shiraz 750ml
description: Named after david wynn's youngest son, wynns michael shiraz is only being produced when the vintage condition in coonawarra is exceptional. it showcases the unique terroir of the region and with the  release, it displays the qualities that really set it apart with other in the same category. with aromas of red currants, cherries and raspberry that mesh every so well with the olive and white spice characters. the palate follows with an elegant structure bursting with dark brooding spice and succulent ripe tannins. provided with the correct conditions, this could easily be a cellar star.

product_name: Tissot Chemin des Tourelles Powermatic 80 Lady Stainless Steel Women's Watch
description: The Tissot Chemin des Tourelles is a very special piece that encapsulates an important part of Tissot's history. It takes its name from the street in Le Locle, Switzerland, where the Tissot factory was established in 1907, and where the company can still be found today. The watch compliments the company's vast years of expertise with a contemporary design with an elegant case. The result is wonderfully luxurious, but still easily accessible thanks to the good value Tissot is still proud to offer. T099.207.11.116.00

product_name: Tissot Le Locle Powermatic 80 Black/Silver Men's Watch
description: The Le Locle Automatic is a range as broad as it is beautiful. PVD coating provides a selection of colours including steel, yellow gold and rose gold colours. Dial designs include some of the watch industry’s most iconic features and the collection offers a choice of details including Clous de Paris, Roman numerals and indexes and even Top Wesselton diamonds or an open heart dial. The see-through case back is engraved with a traditional Le Locle signature as an additional measure of authenticity. It’s a reminder of our long and illustrious history of watchmaking tradition. product_name: Taylors Heritage Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description:
Family-owned and operated, taylors wines rests on the principle that the finest wines are those made with the greatest dedication and care. this limited edition label celebrates their heritage and the commitment of three generations of the taylor family dedicated to making fine australian wine.
nose:
rich blackcurrant, subtle spice, tomato leaf and a touch of eucalyptus.
palate:
fine and elegant tannins, well balanced, and complex, with a lingering finish.

product_name: Tenjaku Pure Malt Whisky 700ml
description: Tenjaku is a Japanese character for both the skylark (Hibari), the beloved herald of spring, and this masterful malt whisky. It has an agreeably pure, mellow flavor, similar to the clear exquisite song of a small bird. The color of this fantastic whisky is pale gold. Aromas of fresh grain, banana bread with raisins, toasted walnuts, and honey-drizzled pears, with a supple, crisp, dryish light-to-medium body and a smooth, interesting medium-long finish of melon, smoked peppercorns, pimiento, marinated mushrooms, and banana nougat.

product_name: Tissot Le Locle Powermatic 80 Rose Gold Men's Watch

Dial designs include some of the watch industry’s most iconic features and the collection offers a choice of details including Clous de Paris, Roman numerals and indexes and even Top Wesselton diamonds or an open heart dial. The see-through case back is engraved with a traditional Le Locle signature as an additional measure of authenticity. It’s a reminder of our long and illustrious history of watchmaking tradition. T006.407.22.033.00

product_name: Taylors The Visionary Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: This pinnacle release Cabernet Sauvignon is crafted from the very finest fruit selection and is entirely estate grown and bottled on the Taylor family estate in the Clare Valley, South Australia. Tasting Notes: Color: A dark red-black core framed by a crimson rim. Nose:  The wine is attractively scented with wild berry and bramble hints backgrounded by light chocolate and mint notes with a subtle smoky cigar air from extended premium oak maturation. Palate: The wine delivers a focused, upfront berry and summer fruits profile that jumps straight to the centre of attention and is counterbalanced by a mouth-watering freshness. There is a ripe and highly integrated tannin and oak firmness to the focused, long finish. This wine has lovely dimensions and a poised, elegance and depth that reflects it’s carefully selected provenance, vinification and cellaring. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Taylors St Andrews Chardonnay 750ml
description: Silky textured with exceptional length and flavours of peach, nectarine and subtle cashew nuances from quality French oak. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine is a youthful pale straw colour with vibrant green hue to the edges. Nose: The wine has ripe white peach aromas along with hints of tropical fruit and subtle creamy oak. Enticing sweet spice and savoury cashew nut from the French oak add complexity to the bouquet. Palate: This is a medium-bodied yet sumptuous wine with an enjoyable creaminess to the mid-palate. Flavours of juicy white fleshed stone fruit are evident along with cleansing citrus at the finish which has wonderful persistence and length from the use of quality French oak. Alcohol:  13.5%

product_name: Taylors St Andrews Shiraz 750ml
description: Enormously flavoursome with rich fruit characters of black cherry, plum and ripe berries. American oak adds nuances of vanilla, cigar box, coffee and toast. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine has a concentrated ruby red colour with a dark purple hue to the edge. Nose: The wine has ripe and concentrated aromas of violets, dark plum and liquorice. Concentrated layers of creamy American oak complex the enticing bouquet. Palate: This is a voluptuous wine with great mid palate expression, layers of flavour and yet great balance. Fresh red berry fruits are cradled across the palate by mocha and vanilla spice flavours from high quality oak. The barrel fermentation results in a wine that has well integrated fruit and oak and harmonious, elegant flavours and a long persistent finish. Alcohol:  14.3%

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Chardonnay 750ml
description: The wine has intense lifted aromas of melon and white peach with underlying subtle savoury notes from the french oak. the palate delivers well-balanced and evenly distributed fruit flavours of classic melon and peach along with underlying creamy notes from the lees stirring. texturally, the wine has a retrained, tight structure overall and yet still displays a measure of subtle creaminess to the mid palate and rewards with well integrated oak. the clare valley parcel delivers mid palate fleshiness whilst the adelaide hills component contributes the restraint and elegance that are typical of this region. overall, the wine has a great palate line with length which lingers long after the wine is consumed.

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Clare Valley Mclaren Vale Shiraz 750ml
description:
At release, the wine has a deep crimson red colour to the centre with a vibrant purple hue to the edges. there are lifted aromas of red berry and cherry fruit along with subtle black olive and spice.
this is a rich, full-bodied wine with intense flavours of ripe red berry fruit, violets and attractive oak characters of roasted coffee beans and dark chocolate.
overall, the wine is well balanced with complex, well-integrated tannins providing the palate with an intense, persistent length.

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: A relatively new addition to the taylors range, the jaraman cabernet sauvignon is part of a range that includes some of the best in the taylors lineup of fine wines. elegant with intense fruit flavours of cherry and cassis along with hints of mint, cedar and spice.

product_name: Taylors Made Pinot Gris 750ml
description: This is an enticing wine with green apple, ripe pear and plush nectarine fruit characters combining with a satisfying hint of spice. Alcohol:  13%

product_name: Taylors Masterstroke Cabernet Shiraz 750ml
description: Shiraz delivers rich and plump dark plum to the mid palate whilst blackcurrent, dark chocolate and mint characters from the Cabernet Sauvignon drives the finish.  Overall a sublimely complex and multi layered wine. Critics Rating: Taylors have always hung their hat on cabernet sauvignon, but it’s interesting how often the classic Aussie blend of cabernet with shiraz comes up trumps. 2017 Vintage - 95 Points - The colour is deep red-purple and there are lifted aromas of dried herbs including thyme, mint, sage … indeed, a full bouquet. The palate is elegant, medium-full bodied, with enlivening acidity, and a certain sinewy mouth-feel. Very appealing balance and length. The mint is subtle and effective. Huon Hooke

product_name: Taylors Masterstroke Shiraz 750ml
description:
The wine has a mouth filling lusciousness, densely packed with generous plum and dark cherry fruit flavours along with subtle floral violet characters and a smack of vanilla underlying the opulent oak expression. Alcohol: 14.5% 
   Critics
  Rating: For the Masterstroke series fruit has been sourced from Coonawarra (Cabernet Sauvignon), McLaren Vale (Shiraz) and then back to their traditional Clare Valley home for the classic Australian Cabernet - 93 Points Angus Hughson.  A hot and dry vintage in McLaren Vale in this wine has created a robust and chewy red. Deeply coloured, it shows brooding blackberry and blueberry fruits with some rocky and white pepper complexity topped by toasted coconut oak. That is followed by a dense and spicy palate with sweet fruits showing underlying power that continues through to a good finish with drying tannins. It is quite a complex McLaren Vale style that will drink well over the medium term.

product_name: Taylors Masterstroke Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: The wine has delicious, haunting flavours of blackcurrant, mint and dark chocolate around a finely tuned and classy tannin structure. Critics Rating: A stylish, well made, deep crimson wine with lovely fresh varietal fruit characters of cassis and mint. Fleshy and flavoursome in the mouth with vibrant tannins. Tasting Panel Winestate Magazine

product_name: Taylors St Andrews Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: Named after the historic property first established by Scottish migrants back in 1892, the St Andrews name died when the property was sold in 1934. In 1995, the Taylor family bought the land back, producing a range of flagship wines since 1999. The Taylors St Andrews Cabernet is classic Clare, made with only quality in mind and well suited to aging for the long term, though short-term consumption is very enjoyable too we can assure you! Tasting Notes: Smell: Deep dark and brooding with hints of cassis, mint, blackberry, dried herbs, dark chocolate and cedar. Taste: Intensely concentrated and very pure with rich, ripe tannins and length to burn.  Palate: On the palate it is a very well-balanced wine with ripe blackcurrant characters intermingling harmoniously with oak characters of cedar and subtle tobacco. There is contradiction on the palate with power and strength in the varietal flavours of cassis and yet also supreme delicacy in the fine boned structure. The tasting experience is completed with long, fine tannins and a wonderful persistent presence on the finish. Alcohol:  14.2%

product_name: Tiffany & Co. Tiffany & Love For Her Eau De Parfum 90ml
description: Tiffany & Love Eau de Parfum for Her is a modern yet feminine floral woody scent. The fragrance opens with a burst of bright and sparkling top notes, beginning with blue basil–a botanical ingredient developed exclusively for Tiffany – paired with grapefruit for an aromatic crispness. The sweet floral bouquet of neroli is at the heart of the fragrance, with a woody blend of blue sequoia, vetiver and cedarwood at the base, creating a faceted and feminine scent.

product_name: Tiffany & Co. Eau De Parfum 75ml
description: The House of Tiffany, renowned for its exquisite and iconic jewelry designs, introduces Tiffany Eau de Parfum, a sparkling floral musk signature fragrance for the modern woman.

product_name: Arnott's Tim Tam Double Coat 200g
description: Arnott's Tim Tam Double Coat biscuits are made with a mouth-watering combination of crunchy biscuit, luscious cream centre, wrapped in a thicker milk chocolate coating.

product_name: Arnott's Tim Tam Classic Dark 200g
description: Arnott's Tim Tam Classic Dark biscuits are made with a mouth-watering combination of crunchy biscuit, luscious dark chocolate centre, wrapped in a smooth dark chocolate coating.

product_name: The Jelly Bean Factory 36 Flavour Gourmet Mix Tube 175g
description: The Jelly Bean Factory are the best sharing snack – but only if there’s enough to share. This tube contains 36 huge flavors, can you guess which flavor? The gourmet beans from The Jelly Bean Factory are made with 100% natural flavors and no artificial colors. The Jelly Bean Factory assortment is gluten free, and gelatine free.

product_name: The Singleton Golden Autumn Orchard Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L
description: Inspired by autumnal orchards with fruity aromas and honied scents. To evoke the season richness, the whisky has been Double Oak Matured in ex-Bourbon and American White Oak casks. The result is a delectable Single Malt, ripe with sweet indulgence. Alcohol:  41.8%

product_name: Tim Tam Original 200g
description: An iconic Aussie biscuit, Arnott’s Tim Tam Original is a unique combination of biscuit, cream filing and chocolate coating. It’s easy to see why Tim Tam is Australia’s most-loved chocolate biscuit.

product_name: Arnott's Tim Tam Chewy Caramel 175g
description: Arnott's Tim Tam Chewy Caramel biscuits are made with a combination of crunchy biscuit, chewy caramel centre, wrapped in a smooth chocolate coating.

product_name: Taylors The Aromantiques Chardonnay 750ml
description: The Aromantiques Chardonnay displays tantalising aromas of fresh apple blossom, jasmine, white peach, nectarine and almonds bringing this elegantly structured Chardonnay to life. This is a light bodied, wine with fresh, vibrant flavours of passionfruit, nectarine, peach and hints of citrus. Alcohol:  12.5%

product_name: Taylors The Aromantiques Rose 750ml
description: The Aromantiques Rosé pair fragrant Clare Valley Grenache and Shiraz to uncover aromas of wild strawberries, succulent watermelon and freshly picked white flowers. Alcohol:  11%

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Sauvignon Blanc 750ml
description: A vibrant and beautifully textured expression of Sauvignon Blanc. This wine is elegantly structured with seductive passionfruit and green apple flavours, fresh herbaceous notes and a subtle touch of minerality. Certified Vegan Friendly. Alcohol:  12%

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Grenache 750ml
description: This is a lighter style red wine with juicy red fruit flavours of raspberry and strawberry along with hints of cinnamon spice. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Taylors Jaraman Pinot Noir 750ml
description: An elegant, perfumed expression of the variety, this wine is well structured, full of juicy red fruit and violet characters, superbly balanced with smooth tannins. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Taylors St Andrews Riesling 750ml
description: Hedonistic and tightly focused, this exceptionally balanced wine displays lemon, lime and a seamless spine of natural acidity leading to a finish of extraordinary length. Tasting Notes: Color: At release, the wine is a very pale green/straw colour with a slight green tinge to the edge. Nose: The wine displays vibrant lime aromas with hints of lemon and faint floral notes. Palate: The wine is quite restrained at release with a linear focus to the palate and purity of fruit flavours. Plenty of fresh lemon/lime juice characters abound with crisp and refreshing lime acidity down the mid-palate. All this is complimented by a persistent and refreshing finish. Alcohol:  12.5%

product_name: Taylors The Pioneer Shiraz 750ml
description: This pinnacle release Shiraz is crafted from the very finest fruit selection and is entirely estate grown and bottled on the Taylor family estate in the Clare Valley, South Australia. Tasting Notes: Color: A striking, dark cherry colour which sits at the mid-point between black and ruby. Nose: Generous and immediately offers sweet, spice characters of fine oak lifting from the glass. These are underscored by fresh, red plum and cherry fruit characters that sit confidently at the heart of the wine. Palate: The palate shows considerable structure. There is much to enjoy now, with vanilla and liquorice root notes in abundance through the mid-palate and layering beautifully onto the back-palate and finish, whilst blueberry and ripe dark plums define the overall heart of the wine. The tannins have a velvety softness to them that is neither bitter nor over-firm, reminiscent of sweet plum skins and reinforcing the sense that this wine shall develop exceptionally well in the cellar. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Taylors Visionary Cabernet 1.5L
description: This unique 1.5l collector's edition magnum features a truly unique hand crafted artisan carry case made from tasmanian blackheart sassafras, kangaroo leather and featuring brass accents. each bottle is also individually hand labelled, hand numbered and accompanied by a hand sewn individual booklet.

product_name: Taylor Made Chardonnay  750ml
description: This Chardonnay is well balanced with citrus and white peach characters, creamy undertones from oak maturation and a long satisfying finish. Alcohol: 13.5%

product_name: Taylor Made Malbec 750nl
description: This Malbec is full of intense dark fruit characters, a hint of plum stone and spicy notes of black pepper create a wine that is medium to full-bodied with a smooth finish. Alcohol: 14.0%

product_name: Taylor Made Rosé 750ml
description: A refreshing Rosé crafted in the Provence style with vibrant red fruits and crisp acidity. Minimal time on skins gives a pale salmon colour and an elegant finish.  Alcohol: 12.5%

product_name: Tissot Bella Ora Piccola Silver/Yellow Gold Women's Watch
description: The Tissot Bella Ora Piccola is a women's watch inspired by the sophisticated Mediterranean style. It was created with the modern woman in mind. The model operates with an ETA 980.153 quartz movement, bearing 11 jewels with an EOL indicator. The silver-gold envelope and bracelet are made of stainless steel, the envelope is additionally PVD-coated. The silver dial of the Tissot Bella Ora Piccola  watch is protected from damage by a sapphire crystal with anti-reflective glass. T103.110.22.033.00

product_name: Tissot Tradition Powermatic 80 Open Heart Black Men's Watch
description: The beauty of the Powermatic 80 movement with its awesome 80-hour power reserve is revealed by the opening at 12 o'clock on the dial as well as through the transparent case back. The dials feature a subtle grain d’orge pattern in the centre and a smooth outer dial ring housing simple indexes and an oversized XII. Sapphire crystal ensures scratch-resistant protection for the dial and a selection of textured leather straps and metal bracelets completes the highly desirable look. T063.907.11.058.00

product_name: Tissot PR 100 Yellow Gold Men's Watch
description: The Tissot PR 100 is a classic watch destined to be worn often and for every occasion. It features the simple and elegant face the collection is loved for, with the pared-back aesthetic symbolising luxury, quality and classic style. T101.410.33.031.00

product_name: Taylors Aromantiques Pinot Gris 750ml
description: The Aromantiques Pinot Gris has delightful aromas of fresh honeysuckle, green pear and honeydew melon. This is a sophisticated and vibrant drop. Alcohol:  12.5%

product_name: Tissot Bella Ora Piccola Yellow Gold Women's Watch
description: The Tissot Bella Ora Piccola is a women's watch inspired by the sophisticated Mediterranean style. It was created with the modern woman in mind. The model operates with an ETA 980.153 quartz movement, bearing 11 jewels with an EOL indicator. The gold envelope and bracelet are made of stainless steel, the envelope is additionally PVD-coated. The White mother-of-pearl dial of the Tissot Bella Ora Piccola  watch is protected from damage by a sapphire crystal with anti-reflective glass. T103.110.33.113.00

product_name: Tissot PR 100 Stainless Steel/Yellow Gold Men's Watch
description: The Tissot PR 100 is a classic watch destined to be worn often and for every occasion. It features the simple and elegant face the collection is loved for, with the pared-back aesthetic symbolising luxury, quality and classic style. T101.410.22.031.00

product_name: Tissot Chemin des Tourelles Powermatic 80 Lady White Leather Women's Watch
description: The Tissot Chemin des Tourelles is a very special piece that encapsulates an important part of Tissot's history. It takes its name from the street in Le Locle, Switzerland, where the Tissot factory was established in 1907, and where the company can still be found today. The watch compliments the company's vast years of expertise with a contemporary design with an elegant case. The result is wonderfully luxurious, but still easily accessible thanks to the good value Tissot is still proud to offer. T099.207.36.118.00

product_name: Tissot T-Touch Expert Solar Black Men's Watch
description: The T-Touch Expert Solar is an important new model in the Tissot range. Tissot’s pioneering spirit is what led to the creation of tactile watches in 1999. Today, it is the first to present a touch-screen watch powered by solar energy, confirming its position as leader in tactile technology in watchmaking. Extremely well designed, it showcases clean lines in both sports and timeless pieces. Powered by solar energy with 20 features including weather forecasting, altimeter, second time zone and a compass it is the perfect travel companion. T091.420.47.057.01

product_name: Tissot Chemin Des Tourelles Powermatic 80 Lady Diamond Women's Watch
description: The Tissot Chemin Des Tourelles Powermatic 80 Lady is a high-quality, ladies' watch. The mother-of-pearl-filled and guilloche-decorated dial is complemented by 32 0.064 carat diamonds and a day-of-the-month date stamp. Sapphire glass protects the dial from negative external influences. The Powermatic 80.111 automatic mechanism set on 23 stones with an 80-hour power reserve is responsible for precise time indication - it can be seen through the transparent caseback. The strap is made of cowhide grained leather styled with alligator skin. The water resistance is 5 ATM. All Tissot watches come with 2 year manufacturer's warranty. T099.207.16.116.00

product_name: Tissot PR 100 Lady Women's Watch
description: True to its name, the Tissot PR 100 is Precise and Robust and a hugely popular family within the Tissot range. These new pieces have been launched to give a more modern look in keeping with the time yet still combining traditional watch design using quality materials and the Swiss reliability of the movement. All Tissot watches come with 2 year manufacturer's warranty. T101.210.22.031.00

product_name: Taylors Heritage Shiraz 750ml
description:
Family-owned and operated, taylors wines rests on the principle that the finest wines are those made with the greatest dedication and care. this limited edition label celebrates their heritage and the commitment of three generations of the taylor family dedicated to making fine australian wine.
nose:
plum, blackcurrant and dark cherry fruits along with a bouquet of subtle mocha and a touch of oakey spice.
palate:
plump and generous, with ripe fruit characters of plum and blackberry. mocha coffee and subtle spice from oak maturation balance the fruit flavours.

product_name: Toblerone Tiny Dark Bag 256g
description: Toblerone Tiny Dark - delicious dark chocolate with honey and almond nougat - offered in a shiny, travel exclusive black bag of 32 individually wrapped snack-sized pieces. Dainty and decadent!

product_name: Toblerone Tiny Mix Bag 256g
description: 32 individually wrapped pieces of delicious Toblerone Milk, White and Dark Chocolate with honey and almond nougat in miniature 8g bars - a travel exclusive bag that's great for sharing or as a gift.32 individually wrapped pieces of delicious Toblerone Milk, White and Dark Chocolate with honey and almond nougat in miniature 8g bars - a travel exclusive bag that's great for sharing or as a gift.

product_name: Toblerone Tiny Crunchy Almond Bag 256g
description: Toblerone Tiny Crunchy Almonds – The iconic triangular milk chocolate with honey and almond nougat enriched with crunchy caramelized almonds and a drop of salt. Perfect to share with your loved ones.

product_name: Tissot PRX Powermatic 80 Green Men's Watch
description: The PRX 40 205 may be slim, but it's a real powerhouse thanks to the Powermatic 80 and the new Automatic Valjoux chronograph movements. The Powermatic 80 movement offers a power reserve of up to 80 hours, which means you can take your watch off Friday evening and put it back on Monday morning, and it is still working with no need to reset or wind. The Automatic A05 Valjoux version offers a 60 hours of power reserve. It's a detail for those who like their free time to be truly free. T137.407.11.091.00

product_name: Toblerone Tiny White Bag 256g
description: Toblerone Tiny White - the iconic white chocolate with honey and almond nougat - offered in a shiny, travel exclusive white bag of 32 individually wrapped snack-sized pieces - a convenient treat for white chocolate lovers.

product_name: Toblerone Tiny Crunchy Almonds Mix Bag 256g
description: The assortment of milk, dark and crunchy almonds chocolates with honey and almond nougat in miniature 8g bars. Travel exclusive bag of individually wrapped snack-sized pieces. Perfect to share with your loved ones. The assortment of milk, dark and crunchy almonds chocolates with honey and almond nougat in miniature 8g bars. Travel exclusive bag of individually wrapped snack-sized pieces. Perfect to share with your loved ones.

product_name: Toblerone White Bar 360g
description: Crafted with the finest Swiss white chocolate, Toblerone - White Chocolate 360g is a masterpiece of confectionery art. The smooth, velvety texture of the white chocolate melts effortlessly in your mouth, releasing a luscious creaminess that tantalizes your taste buds. Every triangle is generously embedded with crunchy almond nougat, adding a delightful contrast of textures and a hint of nutty goodness.

product_name: Toblerone Dark Bar 360g
description: Enjoy toblerone, the iconic triangular chocolate from switzerland with honey and almond nougat. this travel-exclusive pack contains 360g toblerone dark chocolate – a perfect gift for anyone who loves dark chocolate. made in switzerland.

product_name: Toblerone Crunchy Almonds 360g
description: Enjoy Toblerone Crunchy Almonds, the iconic triangular chocolate from Switzerland, with a twist. Beloved Toblerone milk chocolate enriched with crunchy caramelized almonds and a drop of salt that take the taste and texture sensation to a whole new level! This travel exclusive pack contains 360g of Toblerone Crunchy Almonds - a perfect and surprising gift. Made in Switzerland. Ingredients:  Sugar, caramelised salted almonds [almonds (67%), sugar, glucose syrup, salt (2%), milk fat], whole milk powder, cocoa butter, cocoa mass, honey (2.5%), milk fat, almonds (1%), emulsifier (soya lecithin), egg white, flavouring. Milk chocolate contains: Cocoa solids 28% minimum. Milk solids 14% minimum. May contain other nuts. Storage conditions:  Store in a dry place. Protect from heat.

product_name: Tanqueray No. Ten Gin 1L
description:
Charles Tanqueray created the world’s finest London Dry Gin in 1830 and it is made today to the same classic, timeless recipe. Tanqueray No. Ten was created with this heritage in mind and set the standard as one of the very first ultra-premium gins.
 Tanqueray No. TEN Gin is distilled four times with Tanqueray’s standard gin botanicals of refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice. Whole citrus fruits, including limes, oranges and pink grapefruit are then added with chamomile flowers to Tiny Ten, the still from which the liquid gets its name.

product_name: Tanqueray London Dry Gin 1L 47.3%
description: Created by Charles Tanqueray in 1830, Tanqueray London Dry Gin is made today according to the same classic, timeless recipe. Tanqueray London Dry Gin is distilled four times and has the perfect balance of four classic gin botanicals – refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice. It is best enjoyed with tonic water, plenty of ice and a wedge of lime, but can be used as a great base for a wide range of cocktails.

product_name: Talisker Skye Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L
description: Talisker Skye is the latest release from the windswept distillery on the Isle of Skye. Tasting notes:The liquid has been made from a combination of toasted and refill American oak casks to accentuate the citrus and sweeter notes of Talisker, whilst delivering the gentle smoky and salty flavours that are so unique to whiskies from the distillery. Alcohol:  45.8%

product_name: Talisker Dark Storm Single Malt Scotch Whisky 1L Travel Exclusive
description: Talisker Dark Storm Single Malt Scotch Whisky is matured in heavily-charred oak casks for an intensely smoky flavour, designed to capture the wild, untamed spirit of a full-blown storm at sea. Tasting notes:A whisky with extra spice and smoke, matured in heavily charred casks. Alcohol:  45.8%

product_name: Talisker Surge 700ml
description:
Introducing Talisker Surge, a Global Travel Exclusive offering from single malt brand Talisker. The first Talisker variant aged in 100% bourbon casks making it uniquely rich spiced and vibrant.   Made by the sea; flashes of surging spice and rich honeyed berries electrify the palate, while rolling smoke rumbles underneath. Liquid lightning that stirs the soul and sets pulses racing. 
 Taste:  Flashes of surging spice and rich, honeyed berries electrify the palate, while rolling smoke rumbles underneath, before a delicious chili bite surges forward. Liquid lightning that stirs the soul and sets pulses racing. Country of origin:  Great Britain 
 Ingredients:  Water, Alcohol, Barley, Colouring
with colourant
Manufacturer information: Diageo Scotland Limited,Lochside Place 11-12,EH12 9HA Edinburgh,GB Alcohol:  45.8% 
 Warnings:  Drink responsibly Storage conditions:  Store in a cool dry place.

product_name: Talisker 10 YO 1L
description: Talisker 10 Years Old - The classic stalwart of the Talisker family. The perfect companion for when the day is done, smooth, smoky with a comforting afterglow.A classic Island dram from the Isle of Skye. Aged for a minimum of 10 years in American oak casks, this welcome member of Diageo's Classic Malts series has been recognised numerous times for its excellence.

product_name: Suncoast Roasted Macadamia Manuka Honey Nuts 125g
description: These Australian grown Macadamias have been hand roasted and then gently flavoured with honey for a caramelised taste sensation.

product_name: Sun Coast Roasted Macadamia Sea Salt Nuts 125g
description: These Australian grown Macadamias have been hand roasted and then gently flavoured with Sea Salt.

product_name: Suntory Chita Whiskey 700ml
description:
Chita is a single grain whisky was made with diverse unblended
whisky brewing techniques and master craftsmanship
developed over many years at the Chita Distillery in Aichi
Prefecture. It features a light taste and delicately sweet fragrance.
The bottle design features black calligraphy that expresses
the distinctive qualities of Japanese whisky, set on a white
Japanese washi paper label representing the light flavor. Alcohol: 43%

product_name: Suntory Toki Whisky 1L
description: TOKI, Japanese for “Time”, is a vivid blend of Yamazaki and Hakushu Single Malt whisky and Chita Single Grain whisky. Fifth Generation Chief Blender, Shinji Fukuyo, challenges the conventional hierarchy between malt and grain whisky, highlighting the quality of the Chita grain whisky not as a base but in equal standing to the Hakushu and Yamazaki malts. Basil, green apple, and honey on the nose, with grapefruit, green grapes, peppermint and thyme on the palate.  A subtly sweet and spicy finish with a hint of vanilla, oak, white pepper, and ginger. Alcohol:  43%

product_name: St Remy Authentic Xo 1L
description: Multi-award-winning across the globe, St-Rémy XO is a rich and complex brandy. Its French aromatic intensity remains true to the style of the House. Intense and aromatic. Subtle notes of wood and vanilla are enriched with flavours of gingerbread, candied apricots, dates, figs and nuts. The taste is subtly spicy and offers a long finish. Offering multiple layers of flavours that make it remarkable to critics and connoisseurs alike, St-Rémy XO can be enjoyed neat, on ice or in classic cocktails. Alcohol:  40%

product_name: St Remy VSOP Brandy 1L
description: St Remy VSOP is a rounded, balanced spirit that is easy to drink. With its light and subtle nose, St Remy VSOP is excellent served as an aperitif or in cocktails.  Alcohol:  40%

product_name: Toblerone Fruits & Nuts 360g
description: Toblerone Fruit & Nut of Switzerland contains swiss milk chocolate with raisins & honey & almond nougat. Ingredients: Swiss Milk Chocolate With Raisins And Honey And Almond Nougat (10%): Sugar, Raisins (135), Whole Milk Powder, Cocoa Butter, Cocoa Mass, Honey (3%), Milk Fat, Almonds (1.6%), Emulsifier (Soy Lecithin), Egg White, Flavour, Milk Chocolate Contains Cocoa Solids Minimum 28%, Milk Solids Minimum 14%. Allergen: Almonds, Butter, Egg, Milk, Soy

product_name: St Hugo Eden Valley Riesling 750ml
description: Pale gold with vibrant lime hues, the wine has fragrant white florals, green lime and lemon pith. The palate is intense and pure with great length, showcasing flavours of grapefruit and green peppercorn balanced by taut acidity.  Such a great riesling year in Eden Valley. Perfumed and floral with a powdery bath-salts aroma and a spicy mix suggesting a racy palate is coming. Beautifully balanced and precise palate with a very long finish. Distinct lemon scents on the nose with a trace of lime. The palate has such a lovely acid integration. It's a pristine and pure riesling made with a minimalist approach to achieve the wine style. - Ray Jordan, The West Australian- 94 Points Alcohol:  11%

product_name: St Hugo Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: A superb wine - perfectly blended to create a seamless, deep and complex blend with silky tannins and excellent cellaring potential. Rich plum flavours are complemented by a subtle coco notes and smooth structural oak. Plush, firm tannin and fresh acidity support the line and length of the wine to bring balance and vitality. Alcohol:  14.2%

product_name: Smirnoff Blue Vodka 1L
description: A Smirnoff vodka favourite, Smirnoff Blue Vodka has a delicious, smooth taste that your guests will love. Add to any of the classics, such as a Moscow Mule or martini, or spice up your go-to Bloody Mary. Smirnoff Blue Vodka is Kosher Certified and gluten free. Alcohol:  50%

product_name: Sirromet Vineyard Selection Sauvignon Blanc 180ml
description: Colour: pale straw with hints of green. cellaring: drink now. nose: scented citrus and passionfruit, with fresh peas and grassy tones. palate: zesty, young passionfruit sauvignon blanc with tropical and citrus fruits, nice spinal acidity, soft integral green apple and lime zest touches. winemaking comments: picked on medium weight fruit density, clean, soft and quite persistent. aged briefly in stainless steel over yeast lees for some textural interest. a fresh, bright style made to be drunk young.

product_name: Remy Martin Xo 1L
description: Rémy Martin XO is the signature of their Cellar Master, who with his expertise blends up to 400 different eaux-de-vie. His art of blending allows us to express the full aromatic complexity of this XO Cognac Fine Champagne. Alcohol:  40%

product_name: Smirnoff No.21 Red Vodka 1L
description: Smirnoff No.21 Premium Vodka is the number one best-selling premium vodka in the world, with countless years of heritage and unmatched quality sold in over 130 countries. It is triple distilled from grain and filtered ten times through charcoal for an exceptionally pure-tasting, smooth spirit. There is vodka, then there’s Smirnoff.

product_name: Sirromet Vineyard Selection Shiraz 180ml
description: Region: queensland, australia. colour: rich ruby red. nose: pretty floral lift with dark bramble and stewed red fruit notes. palate: a medium-bodied style shiraz with fruit -driven palate of cherry, plum and blackberry. spicy mocha oak notes round out a velvety palate with soft ripe tannins. winemaking comments: aged in a mixture of french and american oak barrels for 6 months, before being carefully blended to create an easy, drinking shiraz with perfect balance of intense fruit and soft tannins. food match suggestion: enjoy with richly flavoured red meats and roasted autumn vegetables.

product_name: Remy Martin Louis XIII 700ml
description: A truly stunning Cognac from Remy Martin. It is blended from around 1,200 different eaux-de-vie from the Grande Champagne appellation, and some of the spirit was distilled more than 100 years ago. Alcohol:  40%

product_name: Toblerone Tiny Gold Bag 256g
description: Toblerone Tiny - the iconic milk chocolate with honey and almond nougat - offered in a shiny, travel exclusive golden bag of 32 individually wrapped perfectly snack-sized pieces.Toblerone Tiny - the iconic milk chocolate with honey and almond nougat - offered in a shiny, travel exclusive golden bag of 32 individually wrapped perfectly snack-sized pieces.

product_name: Remy Martin VSOP Cognac Fine Champagne 1L
description: This is a Fine Champagne Cognac taken from the two best crus - Grande and Petite Champagne. Remy Martin's VSOP stands for elegance and richness. With its golden amber colour (old pale), smoothness and complexity, it is balanced and perfectly mature. 40% Alc./Vol.

product_name: Remy Martin Louis Xiii 50ml
description: A miniature bottle of Rémy Martin's flagship cognac - the Louis XIII. Blended from their finest eau-de-vie and packaged in the distinctive spiky round decanter, this is the crème de la crème of Rémy's range

product_name: Remy Martin Club 1L
description: Rémy Martin is a family story of close to 300 years, with a visionary spirit incarnated by its unique emblem: the Centaur. Since 1724, the House of Rémy Martin has been driven by one quest - to capture the heart of Cognac: Fine Champagne Cognac. In 1985 by André Giraud, Cellar Master of the House of Rémy Martin from 1956 to 1990, decided to create an intense and complex cognac for real men: Remy Martin CLUB, presented in a very iconic bottle with 8 facets referring to the lucky number 8 in China. Alcohol:   40%

product_name: Sandisk USB blade 32gb
description: Take your favorite files with you on the ultra-compact and portable cruzer® blade™ usb flash drive. It's the small, swift way to save and transfer your digital content from computer to computer, or take it on-the-go. Simply pop your pictures, music and other fun files onto the sleek cruzer blade and start sharing with your family and friends.

product_name: Sirromet Lm Assemblage 750ml
description: When owner mr terry morris asked me to create an elegant, super-premium cabernet blend to honour his wife – “lm” being for lurleen morris. this is the third release of this wine, now a sirromet flagship. only the best parcels of fruit and hand-selected barrels are used to create this exciting wine, which will reward carefully cellaring for 15+ years. intense cassis and black plum with rich chocolate and touches of licorice, subtle spice and floral lift. elegant and complex palate with soft berry fruits, plum, currants and spicy mocha notes. soft integrated tannins and supporting charry oak provide excellent structure, while a refined line of acidity ensures length of flavour and texture on the back palate.

product_name: Sirromet Signature Collection Merlot 750ml
description: Colour: rich violet red, with purple hues. nose: a young, elegant merlot showing redcurrant, fruitcake, a touch of spice and cinnamon forest floor fruits, sweet beetroot tones and soft vanillin oak. palate: sourced from blocks 2 and 52 from our seven scenes vineyard, this is a unique granite belt regional merlot style. fruitdriven, with a rich, juicy, mid-palate of intense plums and rhubarb. firm tannins with good intensity and well-balanced oak. merlot has excellent tannin structure, very well integrated across the palate.

product_name: Sirromet Late Harvest 375ml
description: An unusually warm and dry 2 week period in late february allowed the sun-drenched north facing blocks of our night sky vineyard to produce some stunning late harvest pinot gris grapes. the unusual deep amber colour of the resulting wine is a reflection of the deep pink-purple colour of the late harvested fruit. made in the typical french alsatian style, this wine has beautifully balanced luscious natural sugars with bright crisp acidity and long-term ageing potential. the grapes were picked at 16.5 baumé, fermentation is carried out in stainless steel tanks and is stopped when acidity, alcohol and sugar are perfectly synchronised. granite belt, australia dried apricot, honeyed nectarine, with floral notes of honeysuckle and orange blossom. an intense, perfumed style of late harvest sweet white wine, rich, ripe william pear and peach compote with luscious candied cumquat marmalade, toffee and exotic notes of lavender and sweet musk. fine citrus acidity gives length and persistence on the palate.

product_name: Sailor Jerry Spiced Rum 1L
description: Smooth, spicy notes balanced with vanilla and toffee. Sailor Jerry Ltd. produces a 92 proof spiced Navy rum featuring a quintessential Sailor Jerry hula girl on the label. As the bottle is emptied, additional Pin-up girls designed by Sailor Jerry are visible on the inner side of the label. The rum is distilled in the U.S. Virgin Islands. It takes its influence from Caribbean rum, which sailors would spice with flavours from the Far East and Asia to make it more enjoyable to drink. 40% Alc./Vol.

product_name: Toblerone Gold Bar 360g
description: The iconic triangular chocolate from Switzerland with Honey and Almond Nougat (10%)– a perfect gift for anyone who loves chocolate. Made in Switzerland.  Travel exclusive - Toblerone Gold 360g bar.

product_name: Sirromet Signature Collection Sparkling Red 750ml
description: Colour: dark cherry red, violet edges. nose: fresh berries, mocha, lifted candied red fruits palate: a juicy, fruit driven, dark rich intense sparkling red, well balanced, pretty, soft, and showing forest red berry fruit, rhubarb, lite yet textured creaminess, and with a tight bead. winemaking comments: a unique style, using petit verdot works well in sparkling red styles, but to the tannins, the bright vivid colours and the hardiness of the skins. a good grape variety to use for sparkling reds, balance is the key and petit verdot has those balanced requirements.

product_name: Sirromet Signature Collection Shiraz 750ml
description: Region: granite belt 818m elev, australia. colour: rich ruby red, with violet tones. nose: a young, elegant shiraz viognier blend showing red cherry, spiced plums and floral orange blossom notes, with soft vanillin oak. palate: sourced from blocks 26 & 3 from seven scenes vineyard, this is a distinctive granite belt cool climate syrah style; very delicate, with varietal characters of intense cherries and plum, touches of white pepper, and lovely hints of apricot from the viognier. firm tannins, good intensity with balanced supporting french and american oak. this regional blend works well in our granite belt vineyards. we used a cold soak method on the shiraz with 4% ripe viognier fruit added to the crushed red fruit pre-fermentation. cool fermented with both wild and cultured yeasts, then aged in oak barriques for 14 months. food match suggestion: enjoy with pan-fried pork fillet finished off in the oven

product_name: Sirromet Signature Collection Chardonnay 750ml
description: Our premium chardonnay fruit was sourced from seven scenes (80%) & night sky (20%) vineyards in ballandean, with yields down on previous years. seven scenes fruit was harvested from blocks 7, 8 & 67 a little earlier than usual due to hailstorm activity, however the fruit was in excellent condition and very clean. intense aromas of nectarine, fig, peach, rockmelon, vanilla and roasted hazelnuts. a dry, sophisticated style with rich layers of white peach, melon, waxy citrus and ripe green apple. long finish with a fine backbone of acidity that is well integrated with the nutty, toasty oak.

product_name: Shin Classic Whisky 500ml

The vintage has yielded a wine of precision and concentration with effortless aging assured. Spiced blue fruits, fine boned tannins with fully immersed barrel complexity. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Tanqueray Malacca Gin 1L
description: Tanqueray Malacca Gin is based on a recipe developed by Charles Tanqueray dating back to 1839. Botanicals include cinnamon, clove, nutmeg and cardamom but the exact botanicals remain a secret.

product_name: Tanqueray Rangpur Gin 1L
description:
Tanqueray Rangpur Distilled Gin was first created in 2006 by adding rangpur, an exotic citrus fruit from India with the zestiness of lime and the juiciness of mandarin oranges, together with ginger and bay leaves to Tanqueray’s premium London Dry Gin. The latter is still made today according to the same classic, timeless recipe that Charles Tanqueray created in 1830. It is distilled four times to remove any traces of neutral grain spirit and to allow the added flavours of a perfect balance of four classic gin botanicals – refreshing juniper, peppery coriander, aromatic angelica and sweet liquorice – to shine through. 

The result of adding rangpur, ginger and bay leaves to the original premium product is an easy-drinking gin with a citrus twist.  
Back in the 1830s, Charles Tanqueray was not afraid to mix up brave ideas in his own unique style. He invented a gin which is still celebrated to this day. The perfect mix of ingenuity, heritage and hard work.  Tasting notes: Rangpur – an exotic citrus from India – ginger and bay leaves are added to Tanqueray gin. 41.3% Alcohol

product_name: Sony WH-CH520 Wireless On-Ear Headphones White
description: Listen to your music throughout the day without interruptions. The Sony WH-CH520 Wireless On-Ear Headphones are wireless, lightweight and have a battery life long enough to keep up with you. With up to 50 hours of battery life, you’ll have enough power for even long trips away. If your headphones are running low on power, a 3-minute quick charging will give you up to 90 minutes of play.

product_name: Tanqueray Flor De Sevilla Gin 1L
description:
Tanqueray Flor de Sevilla is a unique distilled gin made with Sevilla orange essences and other fine botanicals. Inspired by Charles Tanqueray’s original recipes and the ripening oranges growing on the trees in sun-drenched SEVILLE, the result is a perfect balance of the uniquely bittersweet taste of Seville oranges balanced with the complexity of Tanqueray London Dry Gin. It is best served with Premium tonic and a squeeze wedge of orange.
 Tanqueray's founder, Charles Tanqueray, was an innovator and pioneer in pursuit of the world's finest gin. In this pursuit he sourced botanicals from all around the world and created over 300 recipes. It is thought that his travels to the sun-soaked groves of Spain in the 1860s inspired the creation  of a unique gin liqueur using Seville oranges.
Back in the 1830s, Charles Tanqueray was not afraid to mix up brave ideas in his own unique style. He invented a gin which is still celebrated to this day. The perfect mix of ingenuity, heritage and hard work.   Tasting notes: Made with bittersweet Seville oranges for a fruitful and zesty taste. 41.3% Alcohol

description: The pepperjack range is a tribute to the barossa's rich heritage. our winemaking team has respect for traditional winemaking techniques, yet is also dynamic and imaginative. the pepperjack winemaking team are conscious of modern wine styles and create wines that reflect our passion for this special region. the bold & concentrated fruit flavours of this pepperjack sparkling shiraz make it the perfect partner for special occasions. a modern take on an australian classic, this stylish sparkling shiraz is wonderful when enjoyed with friends and family.

product_name: Penfolds Bin 51 Riesling 750ml
description: The region’s high altitude and cool climate induces riesling with great finesse and elegance with a capacity for long term cellaring. Wine Fitting: Light Bodied White Food Pairing: Seafood Alcohol: 14.5% Region: Eden Valley

product_name: Mt Uncle FNQ Rum Co Iridium 5YO Aged Rum 700ml
description: Tasting Notes:  Heavy and thick, treacle brims off the nose of the rum. Slight spices of cinnamon, brimming with a burnt aroma and a green freshness of crushed sugarcane. Nose opens over time with a minty display covering in caramel fudge tones, the sugarcane laden and brushed with honey. On the palate it is as oily and thick as can be expected from the nose. Trails of sugarcane and spices settle through, the vanilla and caramel fudge flavours interspersed with green herbs.  Alcohol:  40%

product_name: Penfolds Cellar Reserve Grenache Shiraz Mataro Travel Exclusive 750ml
description: Penfolds Cellar Reserve wines are alternative, limited release wines that explore the innovative boundaries of viticulture, vinification and style. Penfolds Cellar Reserve Grenache Shiraz Mataro is sourced from McLaren Vale, where the maritime climate is perfect for ripening these three varietals. An approachable, fruit driven wine style that is versatile with food. Taste:  Texturally interesting, paper/pith. The ancient soils yielding notes of shale and ironstone. Pomegranate acidity provides succulence. Good rainfall in late winter and early spring provided solid foundations for canopy development and mitigated frost risk. From November to harvest it was dry, resulting in lower-than-average yields. Cool weather prevailed over summer with only one hot spell in January. Conditions were near perfect for ripening grapes to their fullest potential. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Penfolds Cellar Reserve Shiraz 750ml
description: Penfolds Cellar Reserve wines are alternative, limited release wines that explore the innovative boundaries of viticulture, vinification and style. This is the first release of a 100% Cellar Reserve Shiraz. The outstanding harvest afforded us an opportunity to source small parcels of high-grade shiraz to craft something different and contemporary. The Cellar Reserve Shiraz is a modern interpretation of this highly coveted varietal, showcasing the tangible benefit of blending across regions. Large format French oak puncheons and well-seasoned vats were used to mature the blend. An altogether new interpretation of our most recognised grape varietal. Pomegranate molasses entices, unfurling across the mid-palate. Mulberry leaf suggestive of cooler fruits. Slatey/granite like tannins create a well-defined and textural palate. Tightly coiled, chalky finish. Pomegranate acidity interplays with structure and texture well, everything in place, complete. Subtle oak character is detected, some spice coming through, although it’s predominantly fruit forward. Near long-term average rainfall in winter and spring provided good soil moisture profiles and encouraged canopy development, while helping to mitigated frost risk. Spring was warmer than average, with some welcome rain during September and October. From November to harvest it was generally dry and warm, with a peak temperature of 38.2°C recorded in McLaren Vale on the 27th of November. For the most part, mild weather prevailed over the summer months with only one short hot spell in January. Three consecutive days of rain in early February freshened up the vines during veraison. Mild conditions from February until harvest were optimal for slow and steady ripening of shiraz grapes. Harvest was an orderly affair, with some exceptional parcels set aside for the Cellar Reserve Shiraz. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Penfolds Cellar Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: Penfolds Cellar Reserve wines are alternative, limited release wines that explore the innovative boundaries of viticulture, vinification and style. It is only in exceptional vintages that we release a Cellar Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon. The vintage is a modern interpretation of this great and noble varietal, showcasing the tangible benefit of blending across complimentary regions. Large format French oak puncheons have been used to mature the blend, providing an alluring framework for the generous, varietally pure fruit. Near long-term average rainfall in winter and spring provided good soil moisture profiles and encouraged canopy development, while helping to mitigated frost risk. Spring was warmer than average, with some welcome rain during September and October. From November to harvest it was generally dry and warm, with a peak temperature of 38.2°C recorded in McLaren Vale on the 27th of November. Mild weather mostly prevailed over the summer months with only one hot spell in January. Three consecutive days of rain in early February freshened up the vines in readiness for veraison. Mild conditions from February to April were near perfect for slow and steady ripening of cabernet sauvignon grapes to their fullest potential. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Penfolds Bin 311 Chardonnay 750ml
description: In true bin 311 style, the vintage exhibits a concentrated fruit spectrum of citrus aromas with a mineral acid backbone. the palate offers pronounced white peach fruits with underlying sherbet and lemon. proactively rich, fresh and assertive. price may vary per state.

product_name: Penfolds Bin 389 Gift Box 750ml
description: Bin 389 was often referred to as ‘Baby Grange’, in part because components of the wine are matured in the same barrels that held the previous vintage of Grange. This was the wine that helped forge Penfolds reputation with red wine drinkers by combining the structure of cabernet sauvignon with the richness of shiraz. Exemplifying the judicious balance of fruit and oak, Bin 389 highlights the generous mid-palate Penfolds in known for. Alcohol:  14.5%.

product_name: Penfolds Bin 23 Pinot Noir 750ml
description: Penfolds bin 23 adelaide hills pinot noir has definitive earthy cherry, cooked beetroot and crushed vine leaves aromas along with subtle dustiness on the nose; softened, silky tannins with lively mixed red fruits flavours framed by nicely balanced acidity throughout impart a velvety texture that leads to a lengthy finish. Tasting Notes: Color:   Fuji-apple red Nose:   An immediate ascent of delicate white strawberry and white raspberry pastille fruits. Yes, overtly cool-climate pinot noir. Quickly following, a garnish of fresh thyme flowers and Hungarian sweet paprika. And something else, admittedly hard to identify – an aroma lying somewhere between saffron and mustard seed. If only spectrophotometer could ... !?! Oak? Perhaps a scent of star anise may be a link? Upon sitting, the faintest waft of pencil shavings confirms a definite Quercus robur or sessiliflora connection. Palate: Medium-bodied. Weight and texture no doubt positively influenced by an appealing glycerolic contribution. Felt like, rather than velvety tannins, with cherry and strawberry fruits inducing a refreshing mouth-watering/salivating grip. ‘Underneath’ - impressions of tilled wet-earth and aligned parsnip/turnip (kohlrabi) flavours. Oak imparts a structural rather than a flavour imprint – was that 17% or 0.17% new oak?! Alcohol:  14%

product_name: Penfolds Lot. 1990 XO Brandy 750ml
description: It has been a long wait - 28 years in the making. Placed in barrels in 1990, Penfolds Lot. 1990 Pot Distilled Single Batch Brandy has been slowly maturing for nearly three decades. Finished with a splash of Penfolds Grandfather Tawny, the result is an exceptional blend that delivers vibrancy and freshness to palate, alongside complexity, richness and indulgence. Tasting Notes: Palate: A combination of marzipan, baked figs, cardamom and cinnamon spice. Soft and round, great intensity with a warming finish Alcohol:  42%

product_name: Penfolds Bin 8 Cabernet Shiraz 750ml
description: Bin 8 cabernet shiraz from penfolds is a red wine produced in australia on various vineyards and in several appellations (mclaren vale, barossa valley, wrattonbully, padthaway, coonawarra). the wine is aged for 12 months in french oak barrels (6% of which are new) and american (6% in new barrels). the bin 8 cabernet shiraz from penfolds consists of a blend of 52% cabernet sauvignon and 48% shiraz. the bin 8 cabernet shiraz 2014 from penfolds has a deep garnet red colour, developing aromas of blackberries and plums on the nose, which blend with more floral (purple, iris) and vanilla notes, along with hints of smoked roast beef. the wine is full-bodied and offers flavours of black fruit and white chocolate cream. the tannins are ripe and round, well framed by ageing in oak and with a complementary acidity. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Penfolds Reserve Bin A Adelaide Hills Chardonnay 750ml
description: Very restrained, tightly coiled. Aromas of custard apple, Granny Smiths, white nectarine, pistachios and cashew nuts. The palate has real drive, held together by a core of taught acidity. Stone fruits provide sweetness, white peaches and nectarines. Poached loquats, almond meal and freshly sliced pear.  Tasting Notes: Color:   Very pale gold with lime green hues Nose: Restrained upon first pour. Induce awakening via a sprightly decant, or vigorous swirl. Primary white peach and assorted stone fruits give way to tempting scents of fresh crème anglaise/pana cotta. Oak (just) evident, yet impressively integrated (80% new?!) Wafts of struck-match prancing above; intense, smoky barrel-ferment notes lurking below. Complexingly challenging – an abundance of character, yet not saturated; aromatically bedazzling, yet not an assault. Palate: Adelaide Hills fruit: soaring and intense white peach fruits and defined natural acidity. Barrel-ferment: an interwoven nuttiness (roasted cashew) and pliant tension. Lees contact: crème brûlée notes, volume and a heightened leesy texture. The acidity noted above is not a defining feature – more of a softer/gentler acidity playing a supporting role – complimentary to texture. An expansive palate that grows – propelled by persistent flavours and textural integrity. Alcohol:  12.5%

product_name: Penfolds Bin 150 Marananga Shiraz 750ml
description: A contemporary wine sees penfold's think outside the box. an alternative shiraz that is structured in french and american, new and old oak. the wine ages gracefully and can peak between the vintage year plus another 15 years. Notes of dark and purple fruits. Fresh satsuma plum and blackcurrants with sweet notes of cinnamon fruit buns. Exotic spices - juniper berries, dried rosemary, sweet paprika. A beautifully balanced wine on the palate. Sweet and savoury nuances. Sweet/tart plum, crème brûlèe creaminess. Fine and chalky tannins. Tasting Notes: Color: Dense black core. Deep purple rim Nose: Our Marananga vineyards lie in the heart of the Barossa Valley, typifying everything we love about Barossa shiraz. Such complexity! So many layers to unfurl. A distinctive ferric nose denotes the ancient Marananga ironstone, hundreds of millions of years old. Also derived from this geology, dusty graphite powder and whetstone, asphalt/hydrocarbon. A walk-through Chinatown... roast duck with plum sauce, Hoisin BBQ pork ribs. Notes of exotic spice, star anis, cardamom, pimento, acknowledging French puncheon influence Palate: As we have come to anticipate, satsuma plums and boysenberries provide a varietal/regional signature. Grippy, ripe and rich tannins anchor a tightly structured frame. Freshly sawn oak. Rye sourdough crust – still hot out of the oven. Toasted pumpkin seeds on grilled haloumi. Sarsaparilla, black cardamom pods and ethereal nutmeg spice. Alcohol:  14.5%

product_name: Penfolds St Henri Gift Box 750ml 14.5%
description: St Henri is a time-honoured and alternative expression of shiraz, and an intriguing counterpoint to Grange. It is unusual amongst high quality Australian red wines as it does not rely on any new oak. Proudly, a wine style that hasn’t succumbed to the dictates of fashion or commerce. St Henri is rich and plush when young, gaining soft, earthy, mocha-like characters with age. It is matured in an assortment of large old vats that allow the wine to develop, imparting minimal, if any oak character.

product_name: Penfolds Nv Club Port Reserve Tawny 750ml
description:
Medium dense tawny with crimson edge. Fresh caramel nutty aromas with a distinctive aniseed lift from the spirit, combined with ripe plum fruits. Soft and mellow. Sweet plum currant flavours align with fine spirit and balanced acidity, creating freshness and length of flavour. A touch of wood-aged nuttiness adds interest without inducing ‘inappropriate’ complexities for this approachable fresh style. Tasting Notes: 
 Color: Tawny red-brown. Nose: The nose is fragrant and well-integrated, possessing aromas of raisined fruit, caramel, subtle vanillin oak and nutty aged complexity. Palate: The palate has a luscious fruit sweetness balanced by drier barrel-matured characters and subtle spirit. The wine has rich flavours of spicy dried fruit, butterscotch and walnuts before a long, lingering finish. Alcohol:  18%

product_name: Penfolds Father 10 Years Old Tawny 750ml
description: If you're a fan of tawny ports you simply have to try a fine australian version too and there is no better place to start than with penfolds father grand tawny. a sumptuous fortified wine of great smoothness and complex nutty, raisiny fruit. a blend of many outstanding tawny components separately matured in seasoned old oak casks, with a minimum blended average age of ten years. the result yields a wine of generous concentration, vitality, exceptional balance of fruit and oak age complexity. the tawny lingers in the mouth, finishing clean and tight. In 1844 christopher rawson penfold planted vines on the slopes of magill to produce fortified wines. By 1881 penfolds was responsible for one third of south australia's fortified wine production. Penfolds grand tawny is a tribute to 150 years of winemaking excellence housed within the bluestone cellar walls of penfolds magill estate. It is a blend of outstanding tawnies matured in small oak casks for an average of ten years. The penfolds tawnies are made in solera systems (stacked blending systems) at penfolds’ kalimna tawny cellars. These wines are all aged in 300-litre hogsheads (oak barrels) that are at least twenty years old when they reach the tawny cellars, having been used for other penfolds wines up until that point. The maturation process deliberately takes place under corrugated iron. At the height of summer the temperature on the top stack can reach 55 degrees; while in winter, the temperature can fall below 8 degrees. these cyclic swings in temperature are vital to the maturation process, as evaporation, concentration and controlled oxidation are all a part of the complex nature of the aromas and flavours. the combination of extended barrel maturation and the penfolds tradition of excellence ensure the 10 year old tawny has exceptional fruit richness, mellow aged complexity and great length of flavour. Alcohol:  18.5%

product_name: Penfolds Bin 169 Cabernet Sauvignon 750ml
description: Created to reflect a contemporary winemaking approach, emphasising both regionality and maturation of cabernet sauvignon in fine grained French oak Critics Rating:  Endowed with a statuesque framework and definition yet leaving flavours alone… a touch of vanillin bean and Coonawarra red brick dust and chalkiness, and dare we say – limestone! product_name: Penfolds Nv Grandfather Rare Tawny Port 750ml
description: Deep tawny with a distinctive yellow-green edge characteristic of extended wood maturation. Classical Penfolds fruitcake, liquorice and vanillin oak flavours with a sweet full and round mid-palate, and a finish that persists on and on. Tasting Notes: Classical Penfolds fruitcake, liquorice and vanillin oak flavours with a sweet full and round mid-palate, and a finish that persists on and on. Alcohol:  20%

product_name: Penfolds Bin 138 Gsm 750ml
description: Bin 138 is inspired by the wines of southern rhône, where shiraz, grenache and mataro are blended to create full-bodied wines. each year fruit for bin 138 is sourced from old barossa valley vines (some more than 100 years old) and matured for 12 to 15 months in seasoned oak hogsheads to allow the different varietals to shine through.  Bin 138 is defined by its distinctive plum, raspberry pastille and underlying spicy notes. Medium-bodied and refined, expect an initial outer husk of berried flavours followed by a mid-palate burst of fruits. it has grenache driven aromatics with cherry and strawberry fondue aromas somewhat indulged by a fairy floss and sherbet dustiness. 14.5% Alcohol

product_name: Penfolds Bin 707 Cabernet Sauvignon Gift Box 750ml
description: Bin 707 perfectly reflects the Penfolds ‘House Style’ through a cabernet sauvignon lens: intensely-flavoured fruit; completion of fermentation and maturation in new oak; expressing a Penfolds understanding of multivineyard, multi-region fruit sourcing.  Full-bodied and with proven cellaring potential, Bin 707 retains a secure place among the ranks of Australia’s finest cabernets. Tasting Notes: Color: Dense red, with a dark core Nose:   The unravelling begins - immediately laden with black olive and rolled cigar-leaf cabernet appeasements. Then allowing the florals to soar - violet, drying and hanging lavender and baby’s breath (Gypsophila to be precise!). Accompanied by bursts of white sea spray (41% McLaren Vale?) and formic (hint of barrel ferment?), iodine/haemoglobin. Beneath the elution throughout - roasted meats/rendered fat in tandem with cinnamon bar/Dijon mustard seed. Palate:   Certainly the sum of its parts… McLaren Vale ➝ front palate plushness, and again, sea spray. Coonawarra ➝ terra rossa red-dustiness, earth. Barossa Valley ➝ a solid core, and a drive that stridently lunges to the back-palate, enhanced by a regional donation of chocolate/cigar. The berried/plum compôte (with nutmeg and custard) flavours of this Bin 707 are difficult to regionally affix. Yet no more so than its oak (100% new!) is difficult to acknowledge. A mid-palate richness clasps onto graphite and layers of discrete regional cabernet tannins … that time will no doubt morph. In every sense, ‘well-connected’. Alcohol:  14.5%

description: The instinctive, human, highly crafted and boundlessly imaginative approach that prada ascribes to the making of fragrance is everywhere present in the ‘olfactory maps’ for both la femme prada and l’homme prada. designed to take the wearer on a voyage through place, memory and time, somehow there appears a sensual meeting point for these distinct female and male fragrances to consummate an aesthetic relationship through experimentation and tradition. as an olfactory chimera, la femme prada is an invitation to emotion. straying from fragrance’s more familiar routes, a sultry journey is evoked by its frangipani wake. this solar note, a hyper-sensual floral, evokes the dewy humidity associated with the faraway flower. the note is interwoven with ylang-ylang, its spice made smooth with beeswax, vanilla and tuberose. a distilled vetiver finishes the fragrance, grounding and rounding its feel.

product_name: Malfy Gin Con Arancia 1L
description:
MALFY Gins are made by Master Distillers, Beppe Ronco and Denis Muni at the Torino Distillati distillery. Located in Moncalieri, in the Piedmont region of North West Italy.

Malfy Gin is made using vacuum distillation also called cold-distillation. This is a relatively new technique in the world of gin production, enabling a lower temperature to achieve evaporation and therefore not altering the composition of botanicals (avoiding heat-related degradation), this way we can keep our botanicals fresh and flavourful.

Carefully selected ingredients are separated into collections and distilled separately to accentuate their flavours. Our citrus botanicals are steeped in alcohol and then squeezed in a traditional basket press, this extract in turn is then distilled with handpicked Italian juniper. The individual distillates are then artfully blended together and cut with Italian water to create our fruit forward style gins. Color:  Deep Ruby Red Nose:  Orange blossom with a background of juniper Taste:  Rich bittersweet citrus, long finish – deliciously complex Alcohol:  41%

product_name: Marc Jacobs Perfect Eau De Parfum 50ml
description: Absolutely perfect just the way you are. With Perfect Marc Jacobs Eau de Parfum for women, the designer sends the message out loud and clear: you don’t need to change a thing.
